name: cyclin-dependent kinase
reaction: ATP + a protein = ADP + a phosphoprotein [RN:R00162]
comment: Activation of cyclin-dependent kinases requires association of the enzyme with a regulatory subunit referred to as a cyclin. It is the sequential activation and inactivation of cyclin-dependent kinases, through the periodic synthesis and destruction of cyclins, that provides the primary means of cell-cycle regulation.

orthologs.K06655: negative regulator of the PHO system
